# =============================================================================
# ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES EXAMPLE - SECURITY HARDENED
# =============================================================================

# üîí SECURITY NOTICE: Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your actual values
# Environment variables provide the most secure way to store API keys and secrets

# =============================================================================
# üö® CRITICAL SECURITY GUIDELINES
# =============================================================================
# 1. NEVER commit .env.local or any file containing real API keys to version control
# 2. Use different API keys for development, staging, and production environments  
# 3. Regularly rotate your API keys (recommended: every 30-90 days)
# 4. Only grant minimum necessary permissions to API keys
# 5. Monitor API key usage for unusual activity and rate limiting
# 6. Use strong, unique passwords and enable 2FA on all service accounts
# 7. Regularly audit and revoke unused API keys
# 8. Never log or expose API keys in client-side code or error messages

